    <text id="B0260T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McCormick makes a statement regarding Madison Taylor, who appears to owe money,
                    but claims he will not be able to pay until he receives money owed to him. The
                    exact circumstances of the issue are not clear from the letter.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Office <abbr
                            expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. &amp;
                        A.L.</abbr><lb/>Sub <abbr expan="District">Dist</abbr> Augusta &amp;
                            <abbr expan="Highland">High</abbr><lb/>Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia"
                            >Va</abbr><lb/>Thomas P. Jackson</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-04-13">April 13 1867</date>
                        <name type="place"><unclear>Goshen</unclear> Augusta <abbr expan="County">Co</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your letter is to hand &amp; <add hand="h1" place="inline">I</add> have seen
                    Madison Taylor who came from Charlottesville to this place &amp; is carrying
                    on a shop here he informs me that he owes a Debt in Charlottesville to man he
                    had hired &amp; has money owing to him <orig reg="there">their</orig>
                    &amp; left his <unclear>afcs</unclear> to meet the same Also informs me that
                    it will be impossible for him to pay before fall unless he collects his debt in
                        <abbr expan="Charlottesville">Charlotte</abbr> he promised me to go to
                    Staunton and see you soon.</p>

                <p>I think the constable at for this District is a man by the name of James Culton a
                    very reliable man. I really dont know who is the officer have been informed <pb
                        n="2"/>he is the man you can direct your letter to the constable at
                    Brownsburg Rockbridge <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>
                    <orig reg="Really">Realy</orig> and fortunately in this Goshen as yet we have
                    had no <orig reg="occasion">acasheon</orig> for an officer but ever long we will
                    find out when the storm comes who shall be able to stand. I
                    <unclear>fully</unclear> the <unclear>cordetes</unclear> of many</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>J. T. McCormick</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
